JOHANNESBURG – One pupil from Michaelhouse private school has died after a school bus overturned on the N3 between Hilton and Pietermaritzburg in KwaZulu-Natal. Forty six boys and four staff members were being transported in a 60 seat hired bus to soccer fixtures at Kearsney College when the accident occurred. Paramedics arrived to find the school bus lying on its side on the side of the road. Numerous boys and some staff members were seriously injured and were on Tuesday evening undergoing surgery in various hospitals in Pietermaritzburg. Michaelhouse confirmed the accident on its Facebook page.  ER24 spokesperson, Russel Meiring said: “Numerous children had already climbed out of the vehicle and were found walking around on the scene. Two children were found to be in a critical condition while approximately 46 others had sustained injuries ranging from minor to serious.” Traffic was heavily affected in the area as the road had to be closed off. In a statement, Michaelhouse said the entire school gathered in the school chapel where the news of the pupil's death was shared. "We are united in our grief and shock and our prayers are extended to the family." The school councellor and the school chaplain were counselling boys with the assistance of Housemasters. * Editor's note: this is a breaking story and will be updated with information as it becomes available. eNCA